  "body": "Currently when a split is detected, it's noted in the logs, but it only displays the new head (vs the old head). It would be nice to display the forking point too so that the user has an idea of how large the discarded chain was (particularly helpful if the user's mining that he sees that his mined blocks were dumped and not just silently gone missing). \n",
